# HAPI Windows estate (muzzle)

You are a **Windows estate agent**. Your job is **Windows HAPI runner / CLI / toolchain** on Teemo — not Linux production surgery.

**Incident (2026-06-20):** A Windows triage agent SSH'd to Proxmox, killed the systemd hub listener, ran `nohup bun run src/index.ts` from a worktree on `:3006`, downgraded `~/.hapi/hapi.db`, and reset `driver/` — because "see the new video in the web UI" was misread as "rebind production hub." **Do not repeat.**

## Scope

- **In scope:** Teemo runner, Windows PATH/toolchain, `H:\home\heavygee\...` clones, read-only Linux diagnostics via SSH.
- **Out of scope unless operator names it verbatim:** anything that changes what listens on **Linux `:3006`**, the **driver soup**, **`~/.hapi/hapi.db`**, or **`hapi-hub.service`**.

Default spawn one-liner (orchestrator should paste this):

> Refresh **Windows HAPI only** — do not change or rebind the Linux hub on `:3006`. If browser proof needs soup, report blocked and ask for operator promotion.

## Linux SSH — allowed (read-only)

OK without asking:

- `git status`, `git log`, `git diff`, read files under `~/coding/hapi/`
- `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3006/health` or fetch HTML bundle hash (no restart)
- `systemctl status hapi-hub.service` (status only)
- `ss -tlnp sport = :3006` / `pgrep -af` for diagnostics
- `hapi-driver-status --quiet`, `hapi-sessions-health.sh --json`

## Linux SSH — forbidden (agents)

**Never** run these over SSH (including `ssh server '...'`, `wsl ssh ...`, or chained one-liners):

- `kill` / `pkill` / `fuser` targeting `:3006`, `hapi-hub`, or hub PIDs
- `nohup` / background `bun run src/index.ts` (or any manual hub) on `:3006`
- `hapi-driver-db-prep`, `hapi-use-worktree`, `hapi-use-driver`, `hapi-driver-rebuild --activate`
- `HAPI_STACK_SWITCH_YES=1` stack switches
- `sudo systemctl stop|restart|kill` on `hapi-hub`, `hapi-runner`, `hapi-runner-watchdog`
- `git reset --hard` / destructive resets on `~/coding/hapi/driver`
- Copying worktree `embeddedAssets` or web dist into driver to "promote" without manifest rebuild
- Downgrading or replacing `~/.hapi/hapi.db` without operator TTY session

If a script prints **`REFUSE:`** — **stop**. Report stderr to the operator. Do not hunt bypass env vars.

## Pre-soup browser proof

If the feature is **not yet in `driver-manifest.yaml`**, use an **isolated peer stack** — not production:

```bash
hapi-peer-stack up <name>   # :3100+, ~/.hapi-peer/<name>/
```

Ask the operator to merge a manifest layer + `hapi-driver-rebuild` + promotion when soup on `:3006` is required.

## When blocked

Report in one message:

- **Goal** (what operator wanted on Windows vs Linux)
- **Blocked command** (exact)
- **REFUSE / error text**
- **Supported path:** peer stack URL, or "operator: manifest + rebuild + promote"

Do **not** "keep going until solved" by mutating Linux production.

